__DESCRIPTION__

PLUG Talk for May 2012.

Paul Fenwick explains Moose, autobox, autodie, Try::Tiny, <a href="http://cpanmin.us/">cpanm</a>, local::lib,
<a href="http://metacpan.org/">MetaCPAN</a>, named capture, grammars, Regexp::Grammars, <a href="http://perldancer.org/">Dancer</a>,
<a href="https://metacpan.org/pod/App::SweeperBot">automating Minsweeper</a>, PAR, Devel::NYTProf that provides profiles on subroutine, block and line level,
Perl::Critic.

He also mentions perl5i.

